  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI confirmation; however, the supporting validation activity is a high-fidelity numerical simulation whose results are argued to be functionally equivalent to bench-top experimental data. The narrative frames the simulation as a surrogate experiment, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', creating an inference-method mismatch against the requirement's requiredVerificationMethod of 'experimental-validation'.",
