      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "NIH prediction comparison — high-fidelity numerical reference",
      "description": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted by the production CFD model was compared against NIH values from a validated high-fidelity DNS/LES reference simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal pump. Agreement within 8% across all five operating points was observed. The analysis team notes that the reference simulation incorporates experimentally-calibrated blood damage coefficients and mesh-independent solutions, and argues that its outputs are 'as good as' experimental measurements for the purposes of hemolysis acceptance. Monte Carlo propagation of inlet velocity and viscosity uncertainties yielded a 95th-percentile NIH below the clinical threshold of 0.01 g/100 L at all operating points.",
      "passFailStatus": "Pass",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean NIH deviation 6.2%; 95th-percentile NIH = 0.0083 g/100L (threshold 0.01 g/100L)",
