        "name": "High-fidelity DNS/LES reference simulation for NIH comparison",
        "description": "A DNS/LES simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal pump was executed at five flow-speed combinations using experimentally-calibrated Giersiepen-Wurzinger blood damage model coefficients. Mesh independence was confirmed via Richardson extrapolation. Monte Carlo sampling (N=500) was performed on inlet boundary conditions and blood viscosity. Outputs were compared against production RANS CFD predictions to assess hemolysis index agreement. This activity is presented as a functional substitute for bench experimental validation.",
        "activityType": "numerical-simulation",
